cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper proposes a method for compressing input representations in neural models for on-device natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses model compression methods, which could fall under cs.LG (Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The proposed convolutional representation could also be considered a computer vision technique, which falls under cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper mentions gains over recurrent representations, which could be related to neural networks and therefore cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
